Extract Sleep Period Columns from Batch Sleep Export

Source: R/extract_sleep_columns.R
extract.sleep.columns.Rd

Extracts essential columns required for sleep period inversion from batch sleep export data: Subject Name, In Bed Time, and Out Bed Time.

Usage

extract.sleep.columns(data)

Arguments

data

Data frame contain batch sleep export data with columns 'Subject Name', 'In Bed Time', and 'Out Bed Time'

Value

Data frame with three columns: 'Subject Name', 'In Bed Time', and 'Out Bed Time'

Examples

sample_data <- data.frame(
  "Subject Name" = c("S001", "S001", "S002"),
  "In Bed Time" = c("09/19/2024 11:00:00 PM", "09/20/2024 10:30:00 PM",
                    "09/19/2024 11:15:00 PM"),
  "Out Bed Time" = c("09/20/2024 07:00:00 AM", "09/21/2024 06:45:00 AM",
                     "09/20/2024 07:30:00 AM"),
  "Other Column" = c(1, 2, 3),
  check.names = FALSE
)

result <- extract.sleep.columns(sample_data)
